> Lentils - renowned for being good source of fibre and a health food staple, they are
> also so easy to adapt and make the base of dish. The HF chefs take you on a culinary
> journey with the warming aromas of cumin, thyme, and the zesty scent of sumac. Delicious..!

Preheat your #grill{} to high. Pop the @British Chicken Breasts{2} on a #baking tray{}. Sprinkle
the @Za'atar{1}(zesty, sumac scented) spice over the chicken. Season with @salt{} and drizzle
on a splash of @oil{}. Rub the flavours into the chicken.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken.

Pop the baking tray under the #grill{}. Grill the chicken until cooked through and golden,
~{15-18%minutes}, turning halfway.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is done when no longer pink in the middle!

Drain and rinse the @Lentils{1}. Trim the @Courgette{1}, quarter lengthways then chop
widthways into small pieces. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Lentils ==

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #saucepan{} over medium heat. Add the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90}(optional)
and cook for ~{2%minutes}, then add the courgette, garlic and @Ground Cumin{1}. Cook, stirring,
for ~{1-2%minutes}, then add the @Water for the Sauce{75%ml}. Bring to the boil then stir in
the @Chicken Stock Powder{1} and lentils. Simmer until the courgette is tender stirring occasionally,
~{5-6%minutes}.

When the chicken is ready, transfer to a #plate{}. Keep to one side.

Stir the @Creme Fraiche{99} into the lentils and bring to the boil. Season to taste with
@salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Share the lentils between your #bowls{} and top with
the chicken. Enjoy!

> Mod Step 4: If you've decided to add bacon lardons to your meal, add to the pan before
> you add the courgette, garlic and cumin and cook for 2 mins. Add the courgette, garlic
> and cumin to the bacon and cook as instructed.